</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD436C2870DAA1246A0FB26DE4BAC1C" blockId="22.[189,1399,1236,1594]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA1246A0FB26DAD5AECB" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1949" box="[189,437,1236,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulifera">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA1246A0FB26DAD5AECB" box="[189,437,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Centris triangulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nom. rev., 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA12445BFB26D806AECB" authority="Friese, 1899" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[582,870,1236,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labrosa">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA12445BFB26D9A5AECB" box="[582,709,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. labrosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33870DAA1244CCFB26D806AECB" author="Friese" box="[721,870,1236,1262]" firstAuthor="Friese" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref20742" refString="Friese H. 1899 (1900). Neue Arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek 23: 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA1245B5FB26DF80AECB" authority="Smith, 1874" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1874" box="[936,1248,1236,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminata">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA1245B5FB26DF20AEC8" box="[936,1088,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. terminata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33870DAA124251FB26DF80AECB" author="Smith" box="[1100,1248,1236,1262]" firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="357 - 373" refId="ref21960" refString="Smith F. 1874. XLIX: - A revision of the genera Epicharis, Centris, Eulema, and Euglossa belonging to the family Apidae, section Scopulipedes. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (ser. 4) 13 (77): 357 - 373. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937408680879" type="journal article" year="1874">Smith, 1874</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
belong to a complex internal lineage of 
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA12443DFB0BD95BAF36" box="[544,571,1273,1299]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA12444FFB0BD992AF37" box="[594,754,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Heterocentris</emphasis>
), which apparently also includes some undescribed species from Central and South America. Unfortunately, a taxonomic revision of this subgenus is not currently available, so the real identity of these species is unclear. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA1245D1FAB1DFE4AF79" box="[972,1156,1346,1373]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labrosa">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA1245D1FAB1DFE4AF79" box="[972,1156,1346,1373]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Centris labrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA1242A3FAB1DE16AF79" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1949" box="[1214,1398,1346,1373]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulifera">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA1242A3FAB1DE16AF79" box="[1214,1398,1346,1373]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. triangulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are different species, but the 
<typeStatus id="54D08860870DAA12440DFA9AD923AFA7" box="[528,579,1384,1410]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
specimen of the latter is almost identical with that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA1242A3FA95DE0FAFA4" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1910" box="[1214,1391,1383,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semilabrosa">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA1242A3FA95DE0FAFA4" box="[1214,1391,1383,1409]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. semilabrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was proposed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA1244F9FA7ED81BAF83" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1874" box="[740,891,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminata">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA1244F9FA7ED81BAF83" box="[740,891,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. terminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33870DAA1245DDFA7EDFC2AF83" author="Moure" box="[960,1186,1420,1446]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Moure" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref21502" refString="Moure J. S., Melo G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo F. 2007. Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure J. S., Urban D. &amp; Melo G. A. R. (orgs) Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region: 83 - 142. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitibrazil." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA124204FA7FDF37AF83" box="[1049,1111,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). Considering the complexity of the problem, I propose to remove 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA124513FA43D8A9AFEE" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1949" box="[782,969,1457,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulifera">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA124513FA43D8A9AFEE" box="[782,969,1457,1483]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. triangulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) from the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA1246A0FA24DA57AFCA" box="[189,311,1493,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labrosa">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA1246A0FA24DA57AFCA" box="[189,311,1493,1520]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. labrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– a synonymy proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33870DAA124461FA24D855AFD5" author="Snelling" box="[636,821,1494,1520]" firstAuthor="Snelling" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref22174" refString="Snelling R. R. 1984. Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American Centridine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History 347: 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1984">Snelling (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, who apparently did not study the 
<typeStatus id="54D08860870DAA1242DEFA24DF96AFD5" box="[1219,1270,1494,1520]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
specimens of the latter species – and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA1247F0FA09D9FDAC31" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1910" box="[493,669,1530,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semilabrosa">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA1247F0FA09D9FDAC31" box="[493,669,1530,1557]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. semilabrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870DAA1245B2FA09DF23AC31" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1874" box="[943,1091,1531,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminata">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870DAA1245B2FA09DF23AC31" box="[943,1091,1531,1557]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. terminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, at least until a taxonomic revision of this group is made that allows to distinguish the limits between each of these species.
</paragraph>
